00:28:41,080 --> 00:28:45,660
♪Is this how it's like♪

556
00:28:45,660 --> 00:28:48,580
♪Where are you♪

557
00:28:53,140 --> 00:28:54,580
(The First Stand-Up Comedy Audition)

558
00:28:55,290 --> 00:28:59,900
♪Sees the outside world
but can't reach it♪

559
00:28:59,900 --> 00:29:04,850
♪Reflections overlap
on the layered glasses♪

560
00:29:05,370 --> 00:29:09,060
♪The view ahead is blurry♪

561
00:29:09,060 --> 00:29:13,680
♪The last train arrived one minute early
at the end station♪

562
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:18,310
♪Find a minute outside the schedule♪

563
00:29:18,310 --> 00:29:22,760
♪Only to realize that nothing
has changed day by day♪

564
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:24,790
♪I am asleep world♪

565
00:29:24,790 --> 00:29:28,720
♪But forget to close the eyes♪

566
00:29:34,180 --> 00:29:35,140
Thank you.

567
00:29:36,370 --> 00:29:38,430
♪I am asleep world♪

568
00:29:38,430 --> 00:29:41,330
♪But forget to close the eyes♪

569
00:29:43,180 --> 00:29:44,900
How about you go home and rest tonight?

570
00:29:44,900 --> 00:29:45,900
I'll stay with Auntie.

571
00:29:47,100 --> 00:29:48,900
It's not convenient for you
to stay with her.

572
00:29:48,980 --> 00:29:50,940
She needs two infusions tonight

573
00:29:50,940 --> 00:29:52,700
and at least two trips to the restroom.

574
00:29:52,700 --> 00:29:53,700
I'll handle it.

575
00:29:55,060 --> 00:29:56,220
Do you want something to eat?

576
00:29:56,420 --> 00:29:57,380
I'll go buy it for you.

577
00:29:58,260 --> 00:29:59,700
I'm not hungry.

578
00:30:07,460 --> 00:30:08,800
I'm just lucky to have you here.

579
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:10,800
Otherwise,
I'll definitely be overwhelmed.

580
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:15,720
That's so fake.

581
00:30:16,380 --> 00:30:18,140
I haven't helped at all.

582
00:30:18,420 --> 00:30:21,220
What's fake about that?
You've helped a lot.

583
00:30:21,620 --> 00:30:22,900
If you weren't here,

584
00:30:22,900 --> 00:30:25,100
my fragile little heart
would've collapsed long ago.

585
00:30:25,100 --> 00:30:26,500
I wouldn't have made it this far.

586
00:30:30,180 --> 00:30:30,890
By the way,

587
00:30:30,890 --> 00:30:32,900
tomorrow afternoon
I need to help my mom transfer

588
00:30:32,900 --> 00:30:34,140
her medical insurance here.

589
00:30:34,420 --> 00:30:36,420
Can you stay with her for me?

590
00:30:36,420 --> 00:30:37,260
Sure.

591
00:31:08,820 --> 00:31:10,340
I forgot this is a hospital.

592
00:31:11,340 --> 00:31:12,180
Sorry about that.

593
00:31:15,380 --> 00:31:17,420
Do you have time?
How about we chat for a bit?

594
00:31:34,140 --> 00:31:35,340
Bed 20, where are you going?

595
00:31:36,180 --> 00:31:37,300
Just getting some fresh air.

596
00:31:37,500 --> 00:31:38,340
Alright.

597
00:31:43,820 --> 00:31:46,140
Auntie, you're a little different

598
00:31:46,140 --> 00:31:47,660
from what I used to think about you.

599
00:31:47,740 --> 00:31:49,140
What did you think?

600
00:31:49,700 --> 00:31:51,000
I thought you were like my mom.

601
00:31:51,700 --> 00:31:53,340
My mom wouldn't be so optimistic.

602
00:31:53,860 --> 00:31:57,460
She'd never say this about herself
if she got sick.

603
00:31:58,380 --> 00:32:01,220
Yeah, your mom is quite something.

604
00:32:01,700 --> 00:32:03,700
I remember when Xiuya made a mistake

605
00:32:03,700 --> 00:32:04,700
at school,

606
00:32:04,900 --> 00:32:07,620
your mom called me
to the administration office.

607
00:32:08,340 --> 00:32:09,900
She scolded me

608
00:32:11,100 --> 00:32:12,460
so sternly.

609
00:32:12,620 --> 00:32:14,900
It felt like she was
about to sentence me.

610
00:32:17,220 --> 00:32:19,500
I think Xiuya's talent for roasting

611
00:32:19,940 --> 00:32:21,460
came from you.

612
00:32:22,140 --> 00:32:23,700
You've got this strong vibe,

613
00:32:24,220 --> 00:32:25,700
like someone who's after freedom.

614
00:32:27,380 --> 00:32:29,100
Are you flattering me?

615
00:32:29,900 --> 00:32:30,740
Well, kind of.

616
00:32:31,420 --> 00:32:33,700
I do want to please you,

617
00:32:34,700 --> 00:32:36,140
but I'm telling the truth.

618
00:32:37,780 --> 00:32:40,500
Since you're being honest with me,

619
00:32:41,300 --> 00:32:43,260
I'll be honest with you.

620
00:32:44,860 --> 00:32:46,620
Yes, you're right.

621
00:32:47,860 --> 00:32:49,700
I am someone who seeks freedom.

622
00:32:51,180 --> 00:32:53,620
Otherwise,
I wouldn't have married Xiuya's father.

623
00:32:54,380 --> 00:32:57,020
Back then, I loved the movie Caravan.

624
00:32:58,500 --> 00:33:00,580
I loved the drifting life.

625
00:33:02,020 --> 00:33:03,300
It was romantic, right?

626
00:33:03,980 --> 00:33:06,340
But now, I have cancer.

627
00:33:07,300 --> 00:33:09,020
Where's Xiuya's father?

628
00:33:11,300 --> 00:33:12,260
Where is Uncle?

629
00:33:13,020 --> 00:33:15,020
He went on an assistance project.

630
00:33:16,260 --> 00:33:17,420
He's stuck in the mountains

631
00:33:17,420 --> 00:33:19,300
in Sichuan because of a collapse.

632
00:33:21,620 --> 00:33:25,020
He missed
every important moment of my life.

633
00:33:27,020 --> 00:33:29,780
He wasn't there when Xiuya was born.

634
00:33:33,540 --> 00:33:35,540
He didn't mean to.

635
00:33:35,980 --> 00:33:37,340
Whether he meant to or not,

636
00:33:38,300 --> 00:33:40,020
that's the reality.

637
00:33:42,060 --> 00:33:43,780
Do you know who paid

638
00:33:44,500 --> 00:33:46,220
for my hospitalization?

639
00:33:48,580 --> 00:33:49,500
It was Zheng Hao.

640
00:33:51,620 --> 00:33:54,020
Your uncle left his bank card at home.

641
00:33:55,540 --> 00:33:56,860
Now he can't come back,

642
00:33:56,860 --> 00:33:58,300
so we can't access the money.

643
00:34:00,740 --> 00:34:02,540
I tried to chase my dreams,

644
00:34:03,300 --> 00:34:04,980
but I ended up living the life

645
00:34:04,980 --> 00:34:06,580
of a non-working housewife.

646
00:34:09,020 --> 00:34:10,300
If it weren't for Zheng Hao,

647
00:34:10,780 --> 00:34:13,540
we wouldn't know where

648
00:34:13,680 --> 00:34:15,260
to get the money for the hospital fees,

649
00:34:15,300 --> 00:34:17,020
let alone a bed.

650
00:34:20,540 --> 00:34:21,380
Auntie,

651
00:34:22,500 --> 00:34:23,980
I can earn the money.

652
00:34:24,860 --> 00:34:27,020
I know, Shi.

653
00:34:27,100 --> 00:34:28,380
I know you can.

654
00:34:28,860 --> 00:34:30,980
But that doesn't help
when you're in urgent need.

655
00:34:31,740 --> 00:34:33,220
When you need money,

656
00:34:33,300 --> 00:34:34,540
it's too late to earn it then.

657
00:34:36,540 --> 00:34:38,020
When you're young,

658
00:34:38,540 --> 00:34:41,300
you always think
you can find a job easily.

659
00:34:42,220 --> 00:34:43,980
But as you get older,

660
00:34:44,540 --> 00:34:47,780
you really lose your competitiveness.

661
00:34:49,740 --> 00:34:50,580
Shi,

662
00:34:51,300 --> 00:34:52,780
if you truly like Xiuya,

663
00:34:53,500 --> 00:34:55,340
find a proper job,

664
00:34:55,340 --> 00:34:56,780
a stable one.

665
00:34:57,060 --> 00:34:59,780
I don't ask for you to be rich.

666
00:35:00,220 --> 00:35:02,780
I just hope you can give Xiuya

667
00:35:04,060 --> 00:35:05,300
a stable life,

668
00:35:06,540 --> 00:35:09,020
a life with security.

669
00:35:17,550 --> 00:35:18,780
Hello, do you know

670
00:35:18,780 --> 00:35:20,500
where the patient in Bed 20 went?

671
00:35:20,700 --> 00:35:21,620
Bed 20?

672
00:35:21,620 --> 00:35:22,460
Yes.

673
00:35:22,460 --> 00:35:24,780
She seemed to have taken the elevator
with a man.

674
00:35:26,940 --> 00:35:29,220
Do you know where they went?

675
00:35:30,940 --> 00:35:31,780
Auntie,

676
00:35:33,300 --> 00:35:35,100
what you said is absolutely right,

677
00:35:36,460 --> 00:35:37,300
but

678
00:35:38,300 --> 00:35:40,620
I feel

679
00:35:41,820 --> 00:35:43,780
like no matter how well

680
00:35:44,260 --> 00:35:45,400
you prepare for some things,

681
00:35:45,780 --> 00:35:47,220
you can never truly

682
00:35:47,220 --> 00:35:48,340
be fully prepared.

683
00:35:49,780 --> 00:35:52,500
You see, we young people like happiness,

684
00:35:52,860 --> 00:35:54,340
so we enjoy the present

685
00:35:54,820 --> 00:35:56,780
and do what we love

686
00:35:56,780 --> 00:35:57,900
and the job we love.

687
00:35:58,060 --> 00:35:58,900
We don't want

688
00:35:58,900 --> 00:36:01,620
to live in fear every day

689
00:36:01,700 --> 00:36:03,100
for things that can't be predicted.

690
00:36:04,740 --> 00:36:06,300
If you were a loner,

691
00:36:06,300 --> 00:36:08,900
you could absolutely say that,

692
00:36:09,780 --> 00:36:12,780
but once you care about someone,

693
00:36:13,780 --> 00:36:15,180
you wouldn't think like this.

694
00:36:16,980 --> 00:36:19,620
You wouldn't want her
to suffer the slightest bit

695
00:36:19,900 --> 00:36:22,100
or face any setbacks.

696
00:36:23,220 --> 00:36:24,260
Of course, I wish Ya

697
00:36:24,260 --> 00:36:27,180
could pursue the life she wants.

698
00:36:28,300 --> 00:36:30,300
Since she was young,
she's been different.

699
00:36:30,700 --> 00:36:32,780
She has her opinions and thoughts.

700
00:36:33,260 --> 00:36:34,460
We're the ones

701
00:36:34,460 --> 00:36:36,380
who forced her down this path

702
00:36:37,260 --> 00:36:38,420
because we, her parents,

703
00:36:38,420 --> 00:36:40,260
didn't have the financial means.

704
00:36:40,820 --> 00:36:42,620
If I had the money to make Ya

705
00:36:42,700 --> 00:36:44,420
live a comfortable life,

706
00:36:44,780 --> 00:36:46,100
I'd definitely let her

707
00:36:46,100 --> 00:36:47,700
chase the life she wants.

708
00:36:47,780 --> 00:36:49,780
She could do whatever she wanted.

709
00:36:50,780 --> 00:36:52,260
Do you have enough strength

710
00:36:52,260 --> 00:36:54,180
to let Xiuya pursue freedom?

711
00:36:54,980 --> 00:36:56,620
Without a financial foundation,

712
00:36:57,500 --> 00:37:00,780
all your enthusiasm
will be defeated by life.

713
00:37:01,460 --> 00:37:03,420
I've suffered enough of this hardship.

714
00:37:04,220 --> 00:37:06,500
I don't want Ya to go through the same.

715
00:37:07,860 --> 00:37:09,780
The other day, Xiuya asked the doctor

716
00:37:09,860 --> 00:37:11,780
about the success rate of my surgery.

717
00:37:12,820 --> 00:37:14,620
The doctor couldn't even be sure.

718
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:17,620
If I'm unlucky,

719
00:37:17,700 --> 00:37:19,780
maybe I won't
make it off the operating table.

720
00:37:22,140 --> 00:37:22,980
Shi,

721
00:37:24,820 --> 00:37:26,100
if you were my son,

722
00:37:26,620 --> 00:37:28,100
I would definitely support you.

723
00:37:29,780 --> 00:37:34,340
But now,
I have to think about my daughter.

724
00:37:51,580 --> 00:37:53,500
Where did you guys go?

725
00:37:54,100 --> 00:37:56,300
Shi took me upstairs for some fresh air.

726
00:38:04,420 --> 00:38:05,500
Have an orange, Mom.

727
00:38:08,900 --> 00:38:10,320
Why does it smell like a cigarette?

728
00:38:14,380 --> 00:38:16,900
I just had one on the balcony.

729
00:38:17,540 --> 00:38:19,820
Don't smoke here in the hospital, okay?

730
00:38:27,260 --> 00:38:28,220
No wonder Mrs. Wu

731
00:38:28,220 --> 00:38:29,780
came to cause a scene in my office.

732
00:38:30,380 --> 00:38:31,540
If she really has cancer,

733
00:38:31,940 --> 00:38:33,380
now it all makes sense.

734
00:38:33,380 --> 00:38:34,380
She had cancer.

735
00:38:34,380 --> 00:38:36,380
Then she found out
her daughter lost her job.

736
00:38:36,460 --> 00:38:38,340
Wu Xiuya and Xu Yunfeng
didn't work out,

737
00:38:38,340 --> 00:38:39,180
right?

738
00:38:39,380 --> 00:38:41,100
Sounds like it.

739
00:38:41,700 --> 00:38:43,300
That's really pitiful.

740
00:38:43,700 --> 00:38:44,940
You don't hate her anymore?

741
00:38:45,340 --> 00:38:47,100
She made our Hao look like a fool.

742
00:38:47,100 --> 00:38:48,220
How could I not hate her?

743
00:38:48,380 --> 00:38:49,820
But what wrong did her mom do?

744
00:38:50,340 --> 00:38:52,220
She only wanted the best
for her daughter.

745
00:38:59,020 --> 00:39:00,220
It smells so good.

746
00:39:00,380 --> 00:39:02,300
Is this the work Hao assigned to you?

747
00:39:02,900 --> 00:39:04,380
It's my fate.

748
00:39:04,550 --> 00:39:05,820
He often visits the hospital.

749
00:39:05,820 --> 00:39:08,160
Aren't you afraid they might
rekindle their old feelings?

750
00:39:08,780 --> 00:39:10,540
I can't control that.

751
00:39:10,980 --> 00:39:13,020
He's dead set on helping her.

752
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:15,100
I'm not worried
about them getting back together.

753
00:39:15,100 --> 00:39:18,540
I'm just worried that he's the only one
putting in effort.

754
00:39:18,580 --> 00:39:20,500
He said he'd rush back after dinner

755
00:39:20,500 --> 00:39:21,940
to deliver the chicken soup.

756
00:39:24,580 --> 00:39:25,420
How about this?

757
00:39:25,780 --> 00:39:27,940
Call him and tell him not to come back.

758
00:39:27,940 --> 00:39:28,780
I'll go instead.

759
00:39:28,780 --> 00:39:29,820
I'll take care of it.

760
00:39:29,820 --> 00:39:30,880
- You go?
- Yeah.

761
00:39:30,900 --> 00:39:31,900
Is that okay?

762
00:39:31,900 --> 00:39:32,980
It's totally fine.

763
00:39:33,220 --> 00:39:34,380
I used to be her boss.

764
00:39:34,740 --> 00:39:35,700
After knowing about it,

765
00:39:35,740 --> 00:39:37,380
it's only right for me to visit.

766
00:39:38,020 --> 00:39:39,380
I won't go alone.

767
00:39:39,740 --> 00:39:41,300
I'll bring the people

768
00:39:41,300 --> 00:39:42,220
close to her.

769
00:39:42,220 --> 00:39:43,060
Don't worry.

770
00:39:43,340 --> 00:39:44,180
I'll handle it.

771
00:39:48,100 --> 00:39:50,020
No wonder you're my best friend.

772
00:39:51,980 --> 00:39:52,900
I'll add meat for you.

773
00:39:53,900 --> 00:40:00,900
(Compassionate, Virtuous,
Sensible, Knowledgeable)

774
00:40:07,420 --> 00:40:09,380
Alright, a bit more. Alright.

775
00:40:10,380 --> 00:40:11,220
Alright.

776
00:40:14,380 --> 00:40:17,100
You don't look like a lady anymore.

777
00:40:17,500 --> 00:40:18,900
You smell now.

778
00:40:18,900 --> 00:40:21,380
Go home, change your clothes,
and take a shower.

779
00:40:22,100 --> 00:40:24,300
No, someone has to be here.

780
00:40:24,340 --> 00:40:25,860
It's just two days. I can manage.

781
00:40:26,900 --> 00:40:28,380
My caravan's downstairs.

782
00:40:28,500 --> 00:40:30,100
The water heater's on. Go take a shower.

783
00:40:30,100 --> 00:40:30,980
I'll stay with Auntie.

784
00:40:31,820 --> 00:40:33,220
You have a caravan?

785
00:40:33,700 --> 00:40:36,260
Yeah, Auntie, I have a house,
a car, and financial freedom.

786
00:40:39,940 --> 00:40:40,820
Go ahead.

787
00:40:43,380 --> 00:40:44,400
I'll get you some water.

788
00:41:00,220 --> 00:41:01,820
Wait. Why is there no water?

789
00:41:07,100 --> 00:41:07,940
Alright.

790
00:41:07,950 --> 00:41:08,940
What's going on?

791
00:41:14,900 --> 00:41:15,960
Ms. Hu, where's the stuff?

792
00:41:16,260 --> 00:41:17,100
It's in the back.

793
00:41:17,460 --> 00:41:18,500
Why are they here?

794
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:20,140
There's more in the back.

795
00:41:23,060 --> 00:41:24,780
Does Manager Hu
have a relative who's sick?

796
00:41:25,940 --> 00:41:26,780
Let's go.

797
00:41:27,380 --> 00:41:28,220
Okay, let's go.

798
00:41:30,900 --> 00:41:32,020
So many people.

799
00:42:16,540 --> 00:42:18,300
They're going to the 4th floor too.

800
00:42:22,060 --> 00:42:23,380
What's going on here?

801
00:42:24,900 --> 00:42:26,740
Hello,
may I ask which room Li Dongmei is in?

802
00:42:26,740 --> 00:42:28,820
She's in Room 409, just behind you.

803
00:42:28,900 --> 00:42:30,380
- Thank you.
- No problem.

804
00:42:35,660 --> 00:42:37,380
(Elevator)

805
00:42:37,380 --> 00:42:38,220
Xiuya.

806
00:42:38,820 --> 00:42:40,540
Why aren't you going in?

807
00:42:48,020 --> 00:42:48,900
Let's go.

808
00:42:49,300 --> 00:42:50,220
Mrs. Wu,

809
00:42:50,300 --> 00:42:51,900
we all came to see you.

810
00:42:53,380 --> 00:42:55,580
Xiuya, what's this new look?

811
00:42:57,340 --> 00:42:59,460
I was washing my hair in the caravan,

812
00:42:59,460 --> 00:43:00,940
but the water stopped halfway.

813
00:43:02,540 --> 00:43:03,380
No way.

814
00:43:04,060 --> 00:43:05,340
Give me the key. I'll go check.

815
00:43:05,340 --> 00:43:06,180
Alright.

816
00:43:06,700 --> 00:43:07,540
Here.

817
00:43:07,540 --> 00:43:08,540
I'll go out for a bit.

818
00:43:11,740 --> 00:43:13,740
Manager Hu, thank you so much.

819
00:43:13,740 --> 00:43:15,820
Look, you even brought so many things.

820
00:43:15,820 --> 00:43:17,860
Mrs. Wu, you're too polite.

821
00:43:17,900 --> 00:43:19,220
No matter what,

822
00:43:19,220 --> 00:43:20,900
we used to be Xiuya's colleagues.

823
00:43:20,900 --> 00:43:22,380
This is something we should do.

824
00:43:22,420 --> 00:43:23,380
Yes, yes.

825
00:43:24,020 --> 00:43:25,500
Xiuya is lucky

826
00:43:25,500 --> 00:43:27,220
to have colleagues like you.

827
00:43:28,340 --> 00:43:30,700
Unfortunately, she's not lucky enough.

828
00:43:30,940 --> 00:43:31,780
Mom.

829
00:43:35,740 --> 00:43:36,580
Manager Hu,

830
00:43:36,580 --> 00:43:39,460
I'm really sorry about the last time
I went to your company.

831
00:43:39,540 --> 00:43:40,820
I acted impulsively.

832
00:43:41,300 --> 00:43:43,220
Sorry for disrupting your work.

833
00:43:43,220 --> 00:43:44,540
Auntie, please don't say that.

834
00:43:44,700 --> 00:43:46,900
We're lucky
to have Xiuya as a colleague.

835
00:43:46,900 --> 00:43:48,540
Right, after Xiuya left,

836
00:43:48,540 --> 00:43:50,220
my workload increased several times.

837
00:43:51,540 --> 00:43:54,380
Xiuya, now I finally understand

838
00:43:54,380 --> 00:43:56,820
the level of effort
and ability you have at work.

839
00:43:58,860 --> 00:44:00,420
If I compare them to you,

840
00:44:00,900 --> 00:44:02,260
they don't even try to compete.

841
00:44:02,260 --> 00:44:04,220
They just lie down, doing nothing.

842
00:44:05,780 --> 00:44:08,380
It's a pity that you resigned
in front of the Chairman.

843
00:44:08,380 --> 00:44:10,700
Otherwise,
I'd have asked you to come back.

844
00:44:11,420 --> 00:44:12,940
Manager Hu, you're joking.

845
00:44:13,540 --> 00:44:15,420
Xiuya, don't be polite with Hu.

846
00:44:15,420 --> 00:44:17,300
- If you could come back, we...
- Alright.

847
00:44:18,220 --> 00:44:19,420
We have so many people here.

848
00:44:19,500 --> 00:44:21,500
We won't disturb your mom's rest.

849
00:44:22,380 --> 00:44:23,220
Auntie.

850
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:24,820
This is just a small gift from us.

851
00:44:24,820 --> 00:44:25,860
How can I accept this?

852
00:44:25,860 --> 00:44:27,380
- This won't do.
- It's nothing.

853
00:44:27,900 --> 00:44:29,380
No, I can't take it.

854
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:31,020
I really can't, Manager Hu.

855
00:44:31,020 --> 00:44:31,860
Xiuya,

856
00:44:31,940 --> 00:44:32,820
this is a small gift

857
00:44:32,820 --> 00:44:34,820
representing our care.

858
00:44:35,100 --> 00:44:35,940
Please accept it.

859
00:44:37,020 --> 00:44:38,300
- We really can't.
- Take care.

860
00:44:38,300 --> 00:44:39,500
Please accept it.

861
00:44:39,540 --> 00:44:40,580
This isn't easy for you.

862
00:44:41,260 --> 00:44:43,380
- Wait.
- We can't help with anything else.

863
00:44:43,420 --> 00:44:44,540
It's the least we can do.

864
00:44:44,540 --> 00:44:45,380
I really can't.

865
00:44:45,380 --> 00:44:46,380
Just take it.

866
00:44:46,380 --> 00:44:47,500
It'll make us feel better.

867
00:44:47,500 --> 00:44:48,220
This chicken soup

868
00:44:48,220 --> 00:44:50,420
is made by Zheng Hao's mom.

869
00:44:50,720 --> 00:44:52,580
- It's her heartfelt gesture.
- We'll go now.

870
00:44:53,380 --> 00:44:54,220
We're leaving.

871
00:44:54,220 --> 00:44:55,780
- I'll see you out.
- No need.

872
00:44:55,860 --> 00:44:57,000
Take good care of your mom.

873
00:44:57,000 --> 00:44:58,120
Really, I can't accept it.

874
00:45:01,380 --> 00:45:02,220
I...

875
00:45:49,500 --> 00:45:51,860
I'll go return the red envelope
to them tomorrow.

876
00:45:56,380 --> 00:45:57,480
Mom, what's wrong with you?

877
00:46:01,060 --> 00:46:02,220
Nothing.

878
00:46:04,780 --> 00:46:06,900
I just think you're too pitiful.

879
00:46:10,340 --> 00:46:11,540
What do you mean?

880
00:46:12,260 --> 00:46:13,540
I'm doing fine, aren't I?

881
00:46:14,900 --> 00:46:16,580
Is this fine?

882
00:46:19,580 --> 00:46:21,220
I'm about to be gone.

883
00:46:24,780 --> 00:46:26,220
If I'm gone...

884
00:46:26,540 --> 00:46:27,900
If I'm no longer here,

885
00:46:28,380 --> 00:46:29,900
who will take care of you?

886
00:46:30,860 --> 00:46:32,700
How will you live without me?

887
00:46:34,020 --> 00:46:35,900
What nonsense are you saying?

888
00:46:37,700 --> 00:46:38,980
You won't be gone.

889
00:46:39,820 --> 00:46:41,420
You still have a long life ahead of you.

890
00:46:43,780 --> 00:46:45,900
I'll also live a great life.

891
00:46:47,180 --> 00:46:49,020
Do you call this a great life?

892
00:46:51,740 --> 00:46:54,940
Your ex-boyfriend's mom
sent me chicken soup.

893
00:46:55,500 --> 00:46:57,940
Your former colleagues brought
all these gifts

894
00:46:57,940 --> 00:46:59,380
and even a big red envelope for you.

895
00:47:00,820 --> 00:47:01,900
They made us

896
00:47:02,380 --> 00:47:04,900
look like beggars.

897
00:47:08,100 --> 00:47:10,220
How can I not worry about you?

898
00:47:18,020 --> 00:47:20,500
But I'll live a really good life.

899
00:47:20,980 --> 00:47:22,500
I'll be just fine.

900
00:47:22,980 --> 00:47:24,860
I will do the work I love,

901
00:47:24,860 --> 00:47:26,220
I'll make a lot of money,

902
00:47:26,220 --> 00:47:28,420
I'll buy a big house for you and Dad,

903
00:47:29,100 --> 00:47:31,700
I'll send you both abroad
to travel the world,

904
00:47:32,300 --> 00:47:33,300
and then I'll get married

905
00:47:33,300 --> 00:47:34,820
to someone who truly understands me

906
00:47:34,820 --> 00:47:36,380
and loves me deeply.

907
00:47:36,500 --> 00:47:37,900
We'll even have a child.

908
00:47:37,900 --> 00:47:39,940
The child will be really cute and smart.

909
00:47:40,380 --> 00:47:41,900
You'll get to see him grow up.

910
00:47:43,820 --> 00:47:45,940
I'll be much happier than you.

911
00:47:46,900 --> 00:47:47,900
Alright.

912
00:47:49,380 --> 00:47:50,940
Stop comforting me.

913
00:47:51,540 --> 00:47:52,940
I'm not comforting you.

914
00:47:54,940 --> 00:47:56,860
I've always thought this way.

915
00:47:57,060 --> 00:47:59,100
What have you always thought?

916
00:47:59,340 --> 00:48:00,980
Do you really think so?

917
00:48:02,340 --> 00:48:03,540
You want to get married?

918
00:48:04,380 --> 00:48:06,540
Who are you going to marry?

919
00:48:09,460 --> 00:48:12,820
Is that Shi Ye?

920
00:48:13,260 --> 00:48:15,540
Isn't he against marriage?

921
00:49:15,321 --> 00:49:19,771
♪Close the comic books,
store apples in the fridge♪

922
00:49:19,771 --> 00:49:23,631
♪Nerves are numb and itchy♪

923
00:49:23,921 --> 00:49:28,421
♪Stop messing around
and put away the smile♪

924
00:49:28,421 --> 00:49:32,321
♪Even mad but don't be forced to smile♪

925
00:49:32,771 --> 00:49:37,131
♪People's characters change♪

926
00:49:37,131 --> 00:49:40,931
♪As time passes and tastes change♪

927
00:49:41,341 --> 00:49:45,801
♪Just laugh without caring for elegance♪

928
00:49:45,801 --> 00:49:49,791
♪Be unique, don't be ordinary♪

929
00:49:49,791 --> 00:49:53,821
♪Let go of lasting memories,
be grateful♪

930
00:49:54,091 --> 00:49:58,421
♪Let go of all struggles
and stubbornness♪

931
00:49:58,421 --> 00:50:02,701
♪Fill the house with freedom. Be free♪

932
00:50:02,701 --> 00:50:06,011
♪Let go of childhood dreams♪

933
00:50:06,011 --> 00:50:09,091
♪And hesitations♪

934
00:50:24,801 --> 00:50:29,191
♪Don't need a broad shoulder
to cry over♪

935
00:50:29,191 --> 00:50:32,921
♪Tears sink into the soil♪

936
00:50:33,291 --> 00:50:37,761
♪Grow into a tree where birds nest♪

937
00:50:37,761 --> 00:50:41,531
♪Passersby, put aside your worries♪

938
00:50:41,791 --> 00:50:45,851
♪Let stars and moon shine
in tomorrow's night sky♪

939
00:50:46,071 --> 00:50:50,121
♪Let sorrows float into the creek♪

940
00:50:50,411 --> 00:50:54,461
♪Let fearless courage flow into the air♪

941
00:50:54,691 --> 00:50:59,191
♪Let the lovely gaze
linger on your face♪

942
00:50:59,191 --> 00:51:03,201
♪Let stars and moon shine
in tomorrow's night sky♪

943
